She wasn't sure just how long she had gazed in steady concentration at the blood but it had been long enough that it filled her vision and would not let in anything more. Her fascination for the simplicity of it wrapping around her attention and holding it hostage to the whimsy of it all. It was after all whimsical to her.<br>
<br>
She slid her dagger from her left hand into the cool brown soil as she crouched to bring her spear closer to her eyes. She rocked slightly on the balls of her feet like a pendulum both heavy and somber and light and strong, coiled tight like a snake ready to strike. <br>
<br>
She reached out her left hand and stretched out her finger to catch the next drip, disrupting it's descent to the green slick grass beneath. She watched it change shape into a small wet bubble until it swelled beyond the boundaries of it's own containment and then spilled over toward the destination she had denied it on its journey. It fell less assured of itself than before, flip flopping and splattering instead of the graceful slide she had watched before. It was the disruption in the pattern that caused the chaos of its fall.<br>
<br>
She stood once more; slipping the dagger back out of its earthen sheath and held it in the cold flesh of her hand. The slow and steady stream of blood was beginning to congeal and she would not see it come dripping down like just before. It was time for more blood. <br>
<br>
Her eyes began to focus on the kin that stood around her. They were the disruption of this place. They were the finger that stretched out and caught the blood of the fallen and scattered it into chaos. They were the ones that stood with her in fascination of the death they brought to those that would oppose them, those that would be sacrificed, those that slid about the world like small blooded jewels in light and shadow, souls clutched safe within their skin. <br>
<br>
She wondered if Myrkul ever stood and watched the souls of their victims slide through the void like a drop of blood, slipping along the same paths until he caught them up on His finger and scattered them in his feeding. Each soul shimmering in light and shadow self contained within their deeds. <br>
<br>
She closed her eyes soaking in the last shadows of the jeweled drops of blood and letting the memory seep beneath her eyes. MORE is all she could think to herself. Her eyes turned inward and she watched the darkness that filled her swell upward toward her vision, clouding her eyes with a black she found comfort in. She felt something cold and wet slide from the corner of her eye in surprise. She reached up and caught it on the tip of her finger turning her vision back to the without. One blackened tear formed into a bubble then slid off her finger to mingle and overcome the blood below...<br>
<br>
As it fell, she thought she nearly heard the sounds of screams of a thousand souls drip down with it...... then silence.<br>
